# Swagger Documentation Patterns

## Controller Annotations

Add Swagger annotations above each handler:

```go
// Index
// @Summary      Get all items
// @Description  Retrieve a paginated list of items
// @Tags         Items
// @Accept       json
// @Produce      json
// @Security     Bearer
// @Param        page query int false "Page number"
// @Param        limit query int false "Items per page"
// @Param        Keyword query string false "Search keyword"
// @Success      200 {object} response.Response{data=[]response.Item}
// @Failure      401 {object} response.Response
// @Failure      500 {object} response.Response
// @Router       /items [get]
func (_i *controller) Index(c *fiber.Ctx) error {
```

## Common Annotations

### Path Parameters
```go
// @Param id path int true "Item ID"
// @Param businessID path int true "Business ID"
```

### Query Parameters
```go
// @Param page query int false "Page number"
// @Param Keyword query string false "Search keyword"
// @Param Status query string false "Status filter" Enums(active, inactive)
```

### Request Body
```go
// @Param item body request.Item true "Item details"
```

### Security
```go
// @Security Bearer
```

### Tags (Group endpoints)
```go
// @Tags Users
// @Tags Orders
// @Tags Products
```

### Responses
```go
// @Success 200 {object} response.Response{data=response.Item}
// @Success 200 {object} response.Response{data=[]response.Item}
// @Success 200 {string} string "success"
// @Failure 400 {object} response.Response
// @Failure 401 {object} response.Response
// @Failure 404 {object} response.Response
// @Failure 422 {object} response.Response
// @Failure 500 {object} response.Response
```

